1
00:00:05,290 --> 00:00:07,680
Hey, you guys. Hey, what are you doing?

2
00:00:07,730 --> 00:00:09,460
Figuring out our wedding plans.

3
00:00:09,510 --> 00:00:11,490
Funny. We were doing the same thing.

4
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:17,450
It's really crazy. The hall, the dress, the food.

5
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:20,040
I had no idea how expensive this was.

6
00:00:20,090 --> 00:00:21,300
Yeah, it is really pricey.

7
00:00:21,350 --> 00:00:23,190
I freaked when I heard the numbers.

8
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,680
So, what did you two do about it?

9
00:00:24,680 --> 00:00:26,060
It was simple.

10
00:00:26,110 --> 00:00:28,190
I came up with some cost-cutting solutions...

11
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:30,910
...wrote out a list, and Monica told me to go to hell.

12
00:00:32,310 --> 00:00:33,730
There's no way around it.

13
00:00:33,780 --> 00:00:36,530
Just accept that this is gonna cost a lot of money.

14
00:00:36,580 --> 00:00:40,040
I heard that weddings are, like, a $40 billion-a-year industry.

15
00:00:40,090 --> 00:00:42,890
Yeah. And I'm responsible for just, like, half of that.

16
00:00:45,150 --> 00:00:48,720
But really, it does seem like this money could be put to better use.

17
00:00:48,720 --> 00:00:50,000
Are you serious?

18
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:51,720
Yeah. How would you feel

19
00:00:51,770 --> 00:00:53,470
if we gave all the wedding money to charity...

20
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:55,890
...and we just got married at City Hall?

21
00:00:55,940 --> 00:00:58,680
I think it would make me wanna marry you even more.

22
00:01:01,040 --> 00:01:04,460
I gotta say, you guys, that's an incredible gesture.

23
00:01:04,510 --> 00:01:06,650
Maybe you do that next time you get married.

24
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:12,260
No, no, no. The next time's gonna be Hawaii at sunset.

25
00:01:13,220 --> 00:01:15,010
But maybe the time after that.

26
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:18,330
《老友记》第十季第七集  领养中心来家访

27
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:58,480
- Hey. What's going on? - Hey.

28
00:01:58,620 --> 00:02:00,910
Our adoption social worker is coming,

29
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:02,490
so we're cleaning the apartment.

30
00:02:02,540 --> 00:02:03,550
"We"?

31
00:02:04,830 --> 00:02:06,760
You know you don't want me to help.

32
00:02:06,810 --> 00:02:08,740
You can't have it both ways.

33
00:02:10,150 --> 00:02:11,520
Is this the person who decides

34
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:12,910
whether or not you get a baby?

35
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:15,600
Kind of. She's coming by to interview us and see where we live.

36
00:02:15,650 --> 00:02:16,970
And it has to go perfectly,

37
00:02:17,020 --> 00:02:18,580
because if she doesn't like something about us

38
00:02:18,630 --> 00:02:19,660
she can keep us off

39
00:02:19,660 --> 00:02:21,030
every adoption list in the state.

40
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:22,410
Hey, maybe I should stop by.

41
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:23,940
She could be a soap opera fan.

42
00:02:24,790 --> 00:02:25,820
It's very impressive

43
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:27,550
when the little people know a celebrity.

44
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:30,420
"Little people"?

45
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:31,800
"Celebrity."

46
00:02:33,610 --> 00:02:35,140
So I think I'm just about done here.

47
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:38,200
Unless you have any bad stuff hidden somewhere,

48
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:40,310
like porn or cigarettes?

49
00:02:40,710 --> 00:02:41,710
What?

50
00:02:43,380 --> 00:02:45,630
- No. - Chandler.

51
00:02:48,730 --> 00:02:49,700
I don't,

52
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:51,800
and I'm offended by the insinuation.

53
00:02:51,850 --> 00:02:55,400
So there's not a magazine under the couch...

54
00:02:55,450 --> 00:02:58,650
...or cigarettes taped to the back of the toilet tank...

55
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:00,970
...or a filthy video in the VCR?

56
00:03:02,310 --> 00:03:04,050
I'll admit to the cigarettes and magazine.

57
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:05,780
But that tape is not mine.

58
00:03:06,170 --> 00:03:07,420
It isn't mine.

59
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:09,240
I guess we'll never know whose it is.

60
00:03:17,940 --> 00:03:18,820
May I help you?

61
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:20,050
Yes. We're here

62
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:22,730
to make a rather sizable donation to the children.

63
00:03:22,780 --> 00:03:24,440
Any contribution, large or small,

64
00:03:24,490 --> 00:03:25,440
is appreciated.

65
00:03:25,490 --> 00:03:26,830
I think you're gonna appreciate

66
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,280
the crap out of this one.

67
00:03:29,220 --> 00:03:30,750
Well, this is very generous.

68
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,430
And we don't want any recognition.

69
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:34,320
This is completely anonymous.

70
00:03:34,370 --> 00:03:36,990
Completely anonymous. From two kind strangers.

71
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:39,500
Mr. X and Phoebe Buffay.

72
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,020
Well if you like,

73
00:03:42,070 --> 00:03:43,440
we can include your names in our newsletter.

74
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:44,300
Not necessary.

75
00:03:44,350 --> 00:03:46,520
Buffay is spelled B-U-F-F-A-Y.

76
00:03:47,650 --> 00:03:51,100
And X is spelled "Mike Hannigan."

77
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:55,370
Well, on behalf of the children, thank you both very much.

78
00:03:55,370 --> 00:03:57,940
I'm glad we did this. It feels so good.

79
00:03:57,990 --> 00:03:59,460
It does. It feels really good.

80
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:02,250
Oh, look. And we get these free T-shirts.

81
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:04,960
Actually, that's the shirt I wore to the gym.

82
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,280
It's moist.

83
00:04:11,330 --> 00:04:13,280
Hi. Emma will be up in a minute.

84
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,150
Oh, good.

85
00:04:14,150 --> 00:04:17,320
Hey, Ross, listen. I heard about you and Charlie.

86
00:04:17,370 --> 00:04:18,260
I'm really sorry.

87
00:04:18,310 --> 00:04:19,640
That's okay.

88
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:22,940
I'm sure there are tons of other beautiful paleontologists out there.

89
00:04:22,990 --> 00:04:23,860
Absolutely.

90
00:04:23,910 --> 00:04:25,910
There was one. She's it.

91
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:28,980
All the rest look like they should live under a bridge.

92
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,680
So, what are you gonna do today?

93
00:04:33,730 --> 00:04:36,040
I was thinking of taking Emma to the playground.

94
00:04:36,090 --> 00:04:38,030
Oh, my God. What?

95
00:04:40,110 --> 00:04:41,500
Like I said, I was thinking of

96
00:04:41,550 --> 00:04:44,810
taking Emma to the Museum of Knives and Fire.

97
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:48,650
Okay, look, Ross.

98
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:52,570
I do not want Emma going to the playground.

99
00:04:56,330 --> 00:04:57,560
Because...?

100
00:04:57,610 --> 00:05:00,990
All right, if you must know, I had a traumatic...

101
00:05:01,530 --> 00:05:04,500
...swing incident when I was little.

102
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:08,130
- Seriously? - Yes. I was 4 years old.

103
00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:09,850
And I was on the swing...

104
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:14,030
...and then all of a sudden my hair got tangled in the chain.

105
00:05:15,650 --> 00:05:16,580
And to get me out,

106
00:05:16,630 --> 00:05:19,720
my mom had to cut a big chunk of my hair.

107
00:05:21,940 --> 00:05:24,300
And it was uneven for weeks.

108
00:05:30,790 --> 00:05:32,800
And you made it through that?

109
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:37,510
I wonder who's gonna play you in the movie.

110
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:40,870
Okay, fine, you can make fun of me.

111
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:43,020
I do not want Emma going there.

112
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,540
Claire Danes:美剧《国家安全》女主角

113
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,540
And I was thinking Claire Danes.

114
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:49,570
Look, I'm sorry to hear about your tragedy.

115
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:51,820
But the swings are perfectly safe.

116
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:53,320
And besides, Emma loves them.

117
00:05:53,370 --> 00:05:55,320
You should come, and you'll see.

118
00:05:55,370 --> 00:05:58,130
Those things go, like, 40 miles an hour.

119
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:00,380
And there's that moment when you're at the top...

120
00:06:00,430 --> 00:06:04,760
...when you just don't know if you're gonna return back to Earth.

121
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:09,500
Space is filled with orbiting children.

122
00:06:12,590 --> 00:06:15,140
Look, please, just come on.

123
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:17,350
When you see the look on Emma's face,

124
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,770
I swear, you won't regret it.

125
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:22,850
- All right. - Good.

126
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:24,500
You don't wanna be a mom

127
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:27,690
who passes her irrational fears to her children.

128
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:29,270
"Irrational," huh?

129
00:06:29,550 --> 00:06:31,290
I'll remember that next time

130
00:06:31,340 --> 00:06:33,140
you freak out about a spider in your apartment.

131
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:35,060
That's the same. I'm sure there are 30

132
00:06:35,110 --> 00:06:37,370
different species of poisonous swings.

133
00:06:41,890 --> 00:06:44,170
Oh, my God. The adoption lady is early.

134
00:06:44,220 --> 00:06:47,210
Okay. Okay. Here we go. Here we go.

135
00:06:47,650 --> 00:06:48,920
Stand up straight.

136
00:06:49,350 --> 00:06:50,540
Big smile.

137
00:06:53,460 --> 00:06:55,850
Hello. Is this the Creepy residence?

138
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:58,530
We're waiting for the adoption lady.

139
00:06:58,580 --> 00:06:59,790
But I'm glad you're here.

140
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,350
I was cleaning this morning

141
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:02,850
and I found this.

142
00:07:03,180 --> 00:07:05,600
I don't know if you wanna use it, but....

143
00:07:06,170 --> 00:07:09,250
Oh, this is so sweet of you.

144
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,480
But you know what?

145
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,600
I won't be needing a veil,

146
00:07:11,650 --> 00:07:13,360
I actually won't be wearing a dress at all!

147
00:07:13,410 --> 00:07:14,120
I told you,

148
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:16,090
I am not coming to a naked wedding!

149
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:18,970
No. We're not having a big reception.

150
00:07:19,020 --> 00:07:20,840
we took the money we were gonna spend on a wedding

151
00:07:20,890 --> 00:07:22,910
and we donate them to the children charity.

152
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,520
That's crazy!

153
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:29,260
I'm sorry. I can't imagine giving up

154
00:07:29,260 --> 00:07:30,940
my one wedding day like that.

155
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,300
Well, we're different.

156
00:07:32,340 --> 00:07:34,560
I don't care about having a huge party.

157
00:07:34,610 --> 00:07:37,010
This is really nice for you, but....

158
00:07:37,060 --> 00:07:40,770
Oh, please. I put this on and I just look like--

159
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:42,020
Well, radiant.

160
00:07:44,950 --> 00:07:46,310
All right, but who cares?

161
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:49,070
I don't need a pretty veil and a fancy dress.

162
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,410
That's right. You're making a commitment.

163
00:07:51,460 --> 00:07:54,610
You know, that's the same whether you do it at the Plaza or....

164
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:56,830
- Where you gonna do it? - City Hall.

165
00:07:56,880 --> 00:08:01,080
Oh, that sounds nice.

166
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,580
I was just there for jury duty.

167
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:05,710
They've really spruced that place up.

168
00:08:06,210 --> 00:08:07,610
Okay. It's okay...

169
00:08:07,660 --> 00:08:10,720
I've made my decision.

170
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:13,800
What I really want is a great big wedding.

171
00:08:16,060 --> 00:08:18,330
But you gave all the money to charity.

172
00:08:18,380 --> 00:08:20,140
Well, I'll just ask for it back.

173
00:08:21,930 --> 00:08:23,340
I don't think you can do that.

174
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:24,310
Why not?

175
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,230
This is her wedding day.

176
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:28,360
That's way more important than some stupid kids.

177
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:30,890
That's sweet, honey,

178
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:33,060
but save something for the adoption lady.

179
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:42,310
- All right, okay. Be careful. - Okay.

180
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:45,350
Careful. Watch her hair. Watch her hair!

181
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:48,930
Rach, she's got, like, three hairs.

182
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:50,420
I know. I know.

183
00:08:50,470 --> 00:08:52,330
But they're just so beautiful.

184
00:08:52,380 --> 00:08:54,560
Oh, my God, I just pulled one out.

185
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:57,200
I promise you she's safe.

186
00:08:57,250 --> 00:08:59,330
Watch how much she loves this.

187
00:08:59,380 --> 00:09:00,120
Okay. Okay.

188
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:02,530
Are you ready, sweetie? Here we go.

189
00:09:04,090 --> 00:09:07,030
Okay, careful. Okay.

190
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:12,930
She's smiling.

191
00:09:13,550 --> 00:09:15,740
Look at that, she does like it.

192
00:09:15,860 --> 00:09:17,560
See, I told you.

193
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:23,950
Oh, my God.

194
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:26,570
Look at her, she's a little daredevil.

195
00:09:26,790 --> 00:09:29,030
Oh, God. Let me push. Can I push?

196
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,880
Oh, absolutely.

197
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:33,430
Oh, God. Okay, get the camera.

198
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,930
It's in the diaper bag.

199
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:36,080
Okay.

200
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:39,060
See? Scared of the swings.

201
00:09:39,060 --> 00:09:40,600
I bet you feel pretty silly.

202
00:09:45,670 --> 00:09:47,740
We're asking for the money back?

203
00:09:47,790 --> 00:09:49,300
It's for our wedding day.

204
00:09:49,350 --> 00:09:51,450
Now, is this guy gay or straight?

205
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,620
Because one of us has to start flirting.

206
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:57,510
You here to make another donation the same day?

207
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:59,450
I don't think that's ever happened before.

208
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:00,930
Gay. Go.

209
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:06,350
Oh, my God, I love your shirt.

210
00:10:08,550 --> 00:10:10,590
The donation we made earlier?

211
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:13,160
Well, we want it back.

212
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:15,460
Excuse me?

213
00:10:15,510 --> 00:10:18,220
Okay, that money was for a big wedding

214
00:10:18,270 --> 00:10:19,460
we thought we didn't want.

215
00:10:19,510 --> 00:10:20,960
But it turns out we do.

216
00:10:21,010 --> 00:10:22,300
So you're asking us

217
00:10:22,350 --> 00:10:24,570
to refund your donation to the children?

218
00:10:24,950 --> 00:10:25,840
Yeah.

219
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:29,260
This feels really good.

220
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:35,110
I'm sorry. I am.

221
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:37,190
But this wedding's just really important to me.

222
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,910
Hey, it's none of my business.

223
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:41,150
Besides, this is probably a good thing.

224
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,810
We've really been spoiling the children,

225
00:10:42,860 --> 00:10:44,760
what with all the food and warm clothing.

226
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:47,930
That's not fair.

227
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,690
A person's wedding is important.

228
00:10:49,740 --> 00:10:51,420
And especially to me.

229
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:53,940
I didn't have a graduation party.

230
00:10:53,990 --> 00:10:55,420
And I didn't go to prom.

231
00:10:55,470 --> 00:10:59,480
And I spent my sweet 16 being chased around a tire yard...

232
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:01,860
...by an escaped mental patient

233
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:03,250
who, in his own words, wanted to:

234
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:04,810
"Kill me, or whatever."

235
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:09,620
So I deserve a real celebration.

236
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:12,560
And I'm not gonna let some sweaty little man

237
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:14,410
make me feel badly about it.

238
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:20,710
She could've been talking about either one of us.

239
00:11:27,630 --> 00:11:28,830
Hi, I'm Laura.

240
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:30,560
I'm here for your adoption interview.

241
00:11:30,610 --> 00:11:33,290
Hi, I'm Monica. And this is Chandler.

242
00:11:33,410 --> 00:11:35,690
- Please come in. - Thank you.

243
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:37,200
Would you like something to drink?

244
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:38,460
Water would be fine.

245
00:11:38,510 --> 00:11:41,180
We're so glad that you're here.

246
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:44,340
We're excited about getting this process started.

247
00:11:44,390 --> 00:11:46,890
Because we love kids. Love them to death.

248
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:49,420
Well, not actually to death.

249
00:11:49,470 --> 00:11:51,060
That's just a figure of speech.

250
00:11:51,110 --> 00:11:53,150
We love kids the appropriate amount...

251
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:56,810
...as allowed by law.

252
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:01,540
- Your place is just lovely. - Thank you.

253
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:04,260
Yes, this building does have a wholesome,

254
00:12:04,260 --> 00:12:05,500
family feel to it.

255
00:12:05,670 --> 00:12:08,160
I feel like I've been here before.

256
00:12:08,210 --> 00:12:10,260
Any other couples in the building adopting?

257
00:12:10,310 --> 00:12:12,090
Is that that couple on the first floor?

258
00:12:12,140 --> 00:12:14,350
Because we should get a baby before them.

259
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,890
That guy tried to sell me drugs.

260
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:19,730
But other than that,

261
00:12:19,730 --> 00:12:21,410
wholesome, wholesome building.

262
00:12:24,290 --> 00:12:25,050
What?

263
00:12:25,270 --> 00:12:27,900
I realized why I remember this place.

264
00:12:27,950 --> 00:12:29,100
Really? What is it?

265
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:30,130
Oh, it's nothing.

266
00:12:30,180 --> 00:12:31,960
I went on a date with a guy who lived in this building.

267
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:34,040
It didn't end very well.

268
00:12:34,460 --> 00:12:37,790
That wouldn't, by any chance, be Joey Tribbiani?

269
00:12:37,830 --> 00:12:40,450
- Yes! - Of course it was.

270
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:43,290
We had a great night.

271
00:12:43,290 --> 00:12:44,840
In the morning, he promised he'd call

272
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:45,920
and he didn't.

273
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,790
Rat bastard!

274
00:12:49,670 --> 00:12:50,670
So you're not friends with him?

275
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:51,600
Oh, God, no.

276
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,810
No, no, no.

277
00:12:52,810 --> 00:12:54,340
No. Nope.

278
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:55,200
No...

279
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:55,880
No...

280
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:56,620
No...

281
00:12:56,620 --> 00:12:57,250
No...

282
00:12:58,840 --> 00:12:59,470
No...

283
00:13:02,150 --> 00:13:04,340
Well, I'm sorry I brought it up.

284
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:07,710
So are either one of you planning on staying at home?

285
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:12,280
Hello? Anybody in there order a celebrity?

286
00:13:15,980 --> 00:13:17,470
What was that?

287
00:13:17,470 --> 00:13:20,460
That's just some crazy guy who roams the halls here.

288
00:13:21,290 --> 00:13:23,250
He's great with kids, though.

289
00:13:30,260 --> 00:13:32,680
Ross. Oh, my God, are you okay?

290
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:34,300
Son of a bitch!

291
00:13:38,430 --> 00:13:41,130
Oh, relax. I didn't say the F-word.

292
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:44,050
Ross, see,

293
00:13:44,050 --> 00:13:46,410
I told you! Those swings are evil!

294
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:47,730
That is it.

295
00:13:47,780 --> 00:13:49,310
That's the last time Emma is getting on

296
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,170
one of those things for her entire life.

297
00:13:51,290 --> 00:13:53,910
No, no, no. Okay, it wasn't the swing's fault.

298
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,230
It was my fault.

299
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:57,570
And kind of that kid's fault.

300
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:01,260
Who is still laughing. Nice.

301
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:03,650
Come on. Can we just get out of here

302
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:05,200
before somebody else gets hurt?

303
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:07,180
No. Wait. Ok, ok. I have an idea.

304
00:14:07,230 --> 00:14:08,820
I want you to get on the swing...

305
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:12,260
...and you'll see that there's nothing to be afraid of.

306
00:14:14,870 --> 00:14:16,720
I know what this is all about.

307
00:14:17,810 --> 00:14:20,040
You've always been jealous of my hair.

308
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:23,500
I just think you're an adult, okay?

309
00:14:23,550 --> 00:14:25,640
And you should get over your silly fears.

310
00:14:25,690 --> 00:14:27,680
All right, fine. I'll do it.

311
00:14:27,730 --> 00:14:28,330
Good.

312
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:29,410
If you hold a spider.

313
00:14:29,460 --> 00:14:30,800
Where?! Where?!

314
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:34,230
If you hold a spider.

315
00:14:34,630 --> 00:14:35,730
I know.

316
00:14:43,350 --> 00:14:44,960
Guys, is everything okay?

317
00:14:45,110 --> 00:14:46,540
It's me, Joey.

318
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:50,200
Adoption!

319
00:14:52,350 --> 00:14:53,520
What's going on?

320
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:56,140
Oh, it's just like I said, that crazy...

321
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:59,530
...Bert, roaming the halls.

322
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:01,230
Guys?

323
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,760
Keep on roaming, Bert!

324
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:06,740
We don't want any crazy today!

325
00:15:07,210 --> 00:15:08,180
What's going on?

326
00:15:08,180 --> 00:15:10,750
We'll talk later! Bert. Everything's fine!

327
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:13,840
Everything doesn't sound fine.

328
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:16,490
Is he all right out there by himself?

329
00:15:16,490 --> 00:15:17,940
Oh, yeah. He has a caretaker.

330
00:15:17,940 --> 00:15:19,260
His older brother...

331
00:15:20,370 --> 00:15:21,840
...Ernie.

332
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:25,660
Bert and Ernie?

333
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:25,660
Bert and Ernie:《芝麻街》里的动画角色

334
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:28,060
You can't make this stuff up.

335
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:31,380
You never told me about that guy

336
00:15:31,380 --> 00:15:32,890
and your sweet 16.

337
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:34,420
I'm sorry about that.

338
00:15:34,420 --> 00:15:35,960
Oh, it ended okay.

339
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,810
One of my friends shot him.

340
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:42,360
At least you'll get a proper wedding.

341
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:43,350
You really deserve that.

342
00:15:43,350 --> 00:15:44,810
Yeah, I really do.

343
00:15:44,810 --> 00:15:47,010
You know, I had nothing growing up.

344
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:52,210
Just like the kids I took the money from.

345
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:55,260
No... I see where this is going.

346
00:15:55,260 --> 00:15:57,220
Don't make me go back there.

347
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:01,240
Look, I can't have a wedding with this money now.

348
00:16:01,290 --> 00:16:02,490
It's tainted.

349
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:05,430
Fine, we'll give the money back.

350
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:06,700
If that guy at the charity

351
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:07,910
gives us a hard time...

352
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:11,110
...my friend hasn't shot anyone in a really long time.

353
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,850
I must say this seems like

354
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:16,700
a lovely environment to raise a child in.

355
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,980
You are welcome to look under

356
00:16:18,980 --> 00:16:19,970
any of the furniture...

357
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:21,030
...because, believe me,

358
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:23,440
you won't find any porn or cigarettes under there.

359
00:16:24,530 --> 00:16:26,050
Before we look around,

360
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:27,420
let me make sure

361
00:16:27,420 --> 00:16:28,460
I have everything I need up to here.

362
00:16:34,770 --> 00:16:36,930
Why don't I show you the baby's room.

363
00:16:42,210 --> 00:16:43,520
What are you doing?

364
00:16:43,570 --> 00:16:44,520
You wouldn't let me in.

365
00:16:44,570 --> 00:16:45,760
I thought you were in trouble.

366
00:16:45,810 --> 00:16:46,640
Well, we're not.

367
00:16:46,690 --> 00:16:48,010
But you called me "Bert."

368
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:51,530
That's our code word for danger.

369
00:16:52,940 --> 00:16:54,840
We don't have a code word.

370
00:16:54,890 --> 00:16:55,580
We don't?

371
00:16:57,030 --> 00:16:58,150
We really should.

372
00:16:58,780 --> 00:16:59,590
From now on,

373
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:02,120
"Bert" will be our code word for danger.

374
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:05,120
So that was the baby's room.

375
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,720
What room should we see next?

376
00:17:08,770 --> 00:17:11,020
Any room that isn't behind this couch.

377
00:17:13,430 --> 00:17:14,910
Some people don't get him,

378
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:16,680
but I think he's really funny.

379
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:26,290
I did not care for that.

380
00:17:27,980 --> 00:17:29,180
You have to leave.

381
00:17:29,230 --> 00:17:30,930
You slept with our social worker

382
00:17:30,980 --> 00:17:32,110
and never called her back.

383
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,230
She is still pissed,

384
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:34,270
so she can't see you.

385
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:35,800
Okay, okay.

386
00:17:39,140 --> 00:17:41,550
- What? - I forgot my bat.

387
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:46,300
Oh, my God.

388
00:17:46,910 --> 00:17:48,180
And for the last time,

389
00:17:48,230 --> 00:17:50,730
we do not want to be friends with you!

390
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:55,260
And we don't wanna buy your bat!

391
00:17:57,570 --> 00:17:59,220
What are you doing here?

392
00:17:59,540 --> 00:18:01,390
Bert...

393
00:18:05,870 --> 00:18:07,260
Are you friends with him?

394
00:18:07,310 --> 00:18:08,500
I can explain.

395
00:18:10,010 --> 00:18:11,010
Joey?

396
00:18:12,380 --> 00:18:13,830
All right. Okay.

397
00:18:18,460 --> 00:18:22,060
You have got some nerve coming back here.

398
00:18:22,990 --> 00:18:24,790
I can't believe you never called me.

399
00:18:24,790 --> 00:18:26,580
Excuse me?

400
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,650
You probably don't even remember my name.

401
00:18:28,650 --> 00:18:30,250
It's Joey, by the way.

402
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:31,420
And don't bother telling me yours,

403
00:18:31,420 --> 00:18:34,510
because I totally remember it, lady.

404
00:18:37,670 --> 00:18:39,200
I waited weeks for you to call me.

405
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:40,280
I gave you my number.

406
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,290
You never called me.

407
00:18:41,340 --> 00:18:43,390
Don't try to turn this around on me.

408
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:47,530
I am not some kind of social work...

409
00:18:47,580 --> 00:18:49,500
...that you can just...

410
00:18:49,550 --> 00:18:50,650
...do.

411
00:18:54,110 --> 00:18:56,570
I'm pretty sure I gave you my number.

412
00:18:56,620 --> 00:18:58,740
Really? Think about it. Come on.

413
00:18:58,790 --> 00:19:00,410
You're a beautiful woman.

414
00:19:00,460 --> 00:19:02,030
Smart, funny.

415
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:04,590
We had a really good time.

416
00:19:06,460 --> 00:19:07,500
If I had your number,

417
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:08,760
why wouldn't I call you?

418
00:19:09,770 --> 00:19:10,780
I don't know.

419
00:19:12,970 --> 00:19:14,230
Well, maybe I'm wrong.

420
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:14,970
I'm sorry.

421
00:19:15,020 --> 00:19:18,630
Hey, too late for apologies. Okay?

422
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:20,290
You broke my heart.

423
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:21,270
You know how many women

424
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,580
I had to sleep with to get over you?

425
00:19:27,020 --> 00:19:28,670
- Joey, wait-- - No!

426
00:19:29,340 --> 00:19:30,400
I waited a long time!

427
00:19:30,450 --> 00:19:31,750
I can't wait anymore.

428
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:37,750
I'm sorry that you had to see that.

429
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:38,770
I'm so embarrassed.

430
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:40,060
Oh, that's really okay.

431
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:42,290
Yeah. We totally understand.

432
00:19:42,340 --> 00:19:43,680
Dating is hard.

433
00:19:44,180 --> 00:19:46,000
Boy, you people are nice.

434
00:19:47,650 --> 00:19:49,210
And I've got to say...

435
00:19:49,570 --> 00:19:52,820
...l think you're going to make excellent parents.

436
00:19:56,850 --> 00:19:58,220
Laura!

437
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:06,670
We're back.

438
00:20:08,230 --> 00:20:09,880
Are you here to take more money?

439
00:20:10,790 --> 00:20:13,150
Because I think what you're looking for is an ATM.

440
00:20:14,060 --> 00:20:16,230
No, no, we're here to give the money back.

441
00:20:16,280 --> 00:20:17,970
Yeah. Because you know what?

442
00:20:18,660 --> 00:20:20,370
It's all about the children.

443
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:23,170
Although it's also about the wedding.

444
00:20:24,430 --> 00:20:25,510
All right, here.

445
00:20:25,610 --> 00:20:26,990
No. Oh, God.

446
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:28,530
If I haven't said so already,

447
00:20:28,580 --> 00:20:30,160
sir, congratulations.

448
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:33,510
Enough, all right?

449
00:20:33,510 --> 00:20:35,510
I'm stepping in and putting my foot down.

450
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:36,340
As your future husband,

451
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:39,070
I'm gonna make this decision for us.

452
00:20:40,140 --> 00:20:42,610
What do you think we should do?

453
00:20:43,370 --> 00:20:46,050
You know what. It's not your decision anymore.

454
00:20:46,050 --> 00:20:46,680
What?

455
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:48,370
On behalf of the children of New York,

456
00:20:48,370 --> 00:20:50,140
I reject your money.

457
00:20:51,010 --> 00:20:52,330
But we're giving you this.

458
00:20:52,330 --> 00:20:54,040
And I'm giving it back to you.

459
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:56,600
Come on. Consider it a contribution.

460
00:20:58,250 --> 00:21:00,490
Well, this is very generous.

461
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,210
Please take the check.

462
00:21:02,210 --> 00:21:03,200
Have a great wedding

463
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:05,270
and a wonderful life together.

464
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:06,800
Sounds good to me.

465
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,700
We can save up, come back in a few years...

466
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:10,000
...and make an even bigger donation.

467
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,750
Absolutely. And when you do, make sure you ask for Brian.

468
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:14,540
- Oh, is that you? - No.

469
00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:20,900
Hello?

470
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:23,470
Oh, hi.

471
00:21:25,040 --> 00:21:27,230
Oh, my God, really?

472
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:29,080
I can't wait to tell Chandler.

473
00:21:29,130 --> 00:21:30,470
Okay. Goodbye.

474
00:21:31,350 --> 00:21:32,570
Wrong number?

475
00:21:33,350 --> 00:21:34,540
That was Laura.

476
00:21:35,180 --> 00:21:36,500
She gave us a great report

477
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:38,490
and we're officially on the waiting list.

478
00:21:38,540 --> 00:21:39,440
That's great.

479
00:21:39,490 --> 00:21:40,570
Now we just wait for a call...

480
00:21:40,620 --> 00:21:41,950
...and someone tells us

481
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,660
there's a baby waiting for us.

482
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:58,030
Hello?

483
00:21:59,180 --> 00:22:00,540
Have you seen Joey's bat?

484
00:22:07,150 --> 00:22:09,800
Okay. I got a spider.

485
00:22:10,190 --> 00:22:12,020
There were two, I picked the bigger one.

486
00:22:13,740 --> 00:22:15,600
- Okay. - Okay.

487
00:22:19,670 --> 00:22:21,930
This feels perfectly normal.

488
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:24,760
Okay, get on the swing.

489
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,520
Okay.

490
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:32,190
Okay.

491
00:22:37,860 --> 00:22:38,840
Okay.

492
00:22:46,830 --> 00:22:47,720
See?

493
00:22:47,770 --> 00:22:50,000
All right. I can do this.

494
00:22:50,050 --> 00:22:52,060
There you go. Good for you.

495
00:22:52,110 --> 00:22:54,510
You know what? I'm getting used to this little guy.

496
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:56,930
I don't even feel him in here anymore.

497
00:22:56,980 --> 00:22:58,590
That's because he's on your neck.

